text: This game isn't going to release for a while on consoles. Everyone who is saying sometime this year I really don't think so. I have this game on PC and its still unoptimized. I run this game at 4K at 30-40 FPS maxed and even as low as 25 FPS. At 1080p maxed the game is still buggy at 40-50 FPS with major dips here and there. This game is also missing quite a bit of content that still needs to be added. The game is only on Alpha 0.35d so if you want to play the game now get a PC with at least 2GB of VRAM on your GPU and that your CPU is at least 3.0ghz so a i5 or i7 with 8GB of RAM DDR3 or DDR4.   My Specs Are:  CPU: i7 5930k  GPU: Titan X  RAM: 16GB DDR4  If the game is running somewhat poorly maxed at 1080p with those specs it needs some optimization. Expect a console release sometime in 2017 maybe late 2016. Hopefully there will be cross platform it would be great to play with friends on other platforms.

text: I play it on PC every now and then, so here's a quick update for you guys (who don't own a PC): - The latest version is 0.52b (at the time writing this comment) - The story has finally got an end, yes the game CAN be completed now. - Still plenty of bugs to fix. (And I mean PLEEEENTY of bugs) - The multiplayer has it's own huge bugs, sometimes it's a mess. - Horrible performance issues still exists, even on some med-high end PCs.   (At this point I highly doubt this will be fixed, it's maybe the engine's fault) - More content required. (Yes, building structures and exploring caves are fun, but I think the game needs more content over those aspects). - Don't forget that the developer team consists 4 people. At this pace they need a few more YEARS before this can be released even on PC. Then it gets ported to PS4...ehh, they gonna need a LOT of time. - If I were you I wouldn't wait for this game to come out on PS4. I have a PS4 too but I doubt it will see the light of day on console.  P.s.: I don't want to make you sad or angry. These are my honest opinions, if you want to play this game, then buy it on PC.
